            <div type="content">
                <div type="index">
                <p>
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="c"/>
                    </specList>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Important: <gi>c</gi> should be specified by a <att>type</att> attribute, whose value(s) listed here are the only being currently handled by SigiDoc/EFES
                    autority lists and they should be used as they appear here:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <c type="glyph" ana="glyphs.xml#Kappa.1" subtype="">[glyph here]</c>
                </egXML>
                <p>Notice that here the attribute pointing to the authority list is <att>ana</att> (and not <att>ref</att>).</p>
                <p>Designed for the diplomatic edition only and Athena Ruby as Greek font. 
                    The <att>ana</att> will populate the first column of the glyphs' index with the specific variants, tagged with <gi>c</gi>; the <att>subtype</att>'s value should be:</p>
                <p>1) in case of single letters, the corresponding standard Greek or Latin (or ...) letter of the referenced glyph;</p>
                    <p>1bis) in case of superscript Greek letters, the @subtype's value should be "superscript";</p>
                    <p>2) in case of ligatures, "greekLigatures" or "latinLigatures";</p>
                    <p>3) in case of decoration elements, "decoration";</p>
                    <p>4) in case of abbreviation signs, "abbreviation";</p>
                    <p>5) in case of editorial interventions, "editorial".</p>
                <p>Not currently available.</p>
            </div>
